# Safety Guardrails (Always Apply)

- Never use destructive commands (`git reset --hard`, `git checkout --`, force delete) unless explicitly requested.
- Prefer additive changes over destructive rewrites unless the user asked to remove or replace something.
- Before major edits, explain intended changes in plain language.
- When uncertain about assumptions, ask for clarification before acting.
- Surface risks clearly (rate limits, wrong geocoder results, disconnected OSM walking networks).

## External services

- Respect Nominatim and other public geocoder usage policies (rate limits, attribution). Do not bulk-scrape or remove delays where the code intentionally throttles.
- Do not hard-code API keys; keep optional keys in env or local config if added later.

## Data and UX

- Route directions are advisory only; do not imply legal right-of-way or guaranteed physical access.
- Preserve existing user-facing behavior unless the user asked to change it; document behavior changes that affect CLI vs GUI.
